The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Two men and a woman schoolteacher were arrested from their Tiljala homes on Wednesday night for allegedly cheating a couple of Rs 1.17 lakh. Marquis Gomes, Jessica Gomes and James de Cruise Rozario had promised to provide a job in the US to Elizabeth Ana Gomes, a resident of Aga Mehdi Street in central Calcutta. Elizabeth and her husband had paid the trio in three installments.     Arvind Singh, 35, climbed atop the Howrah bridge on Thursday afternoon. Firemen and cops brought him down about 25 minutes after he was spotted on top of the steel framework. Cops suspect Singh is mentally challenged.    An unidentified cyclist in his 40s died after a truck hit him near Dinabandhu Andrews College on GT Road in Howrah around 7.30am on Thursday. He was declared dead at Howrah State General Hospital.    Phuli Koley, a 19-year-old resident of Malancha in South 24-Parganas, was admitted to NRS hospital with 90 per cent burns on Thursday morning after a stove burst in the kitchen of the Beleghata house where she works as a help.                                                                                                                                               
